    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "# Zee — Movie Recommender System\n",
        "**Author: Mateenah Jahan Woolf University Malta 
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "## Problem Statement\n",
        "\n",
        "Zee (an OTT / streaming platform) wants to improve user experience and engagement by\n",
        "showing each user personalized movie recommendations instead of generic, one-size-fits-all\n",
        "suggestions. The platform has historical data of movie ratings given by thousands of users,\n",
        "along with user demographic details and movie metadata.\n",
        "\n",
        "The core problem is that with thousands of movies available, users struggle to discover\n",
        "content they will actually enjoy. This leads to poor engagement, more time spent searching,\n",
        "and a higher chance that users leave the platform.\n",
        "\n",
        "The goal is to leverage the ratings given by a user — and by other users who are *similar*\n",
        "to them — to predict what movies a given user is most likely to enjoy, and recommend those\n",
        "movies to them.\n",
        "\n",
        "This is a classic **Collaborative Filtering** based **Recommender System** problem.\n",
        "\n",
        "## Objective\n",
        "\n",
        "The objective of this case study is to design and build a recommender system that suggests\n",
        "personalized movie recommendations. Specifically, we aim to:\n",
        "\n",
        "1. Read, format and merge the three data files (ratings, users, movies) into a single\n",
        "   workable dataframe.\n",
        "2. Perform Exploratory Data Analys"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "zdZPLrqUjrlX"
      }
    },
    {
