      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Recommender System using Pearson Correlation (Item-based)\n",
        "\n",
        "We create a pivot table (matrix) of **users (rows) × movie titles (columns)** where each\n",
        "cell is the rating. Most cells will be empty (NaN) because no user rates every movie —\n",
        "this is a sparse matrix.\n",
        "\n",
        "To recommend movies similar to a given movie, we compute the **Pearson Correlation**\n",
        "between that movie's rating column and every other movie's rating column. Movies whose\n",
        "ratings move together (high positive correlation) are considered \"similar\". We also filter\n",
        "out movies with too few ratings to avoid unreliable correlations."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "O-3TYx8PpUZR"
      }
    },
