    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Recommender System using Cosine Similarity (Nearest Neighbors)\n",
        "\n",
        "Cosine similarity measures the angle between two rating vectors (ranges 0 to 1 for\n",
        "non-negative ratings; in general -1 to 1). Unlike Pearson, it does not subtract the mean.\n",
        "\n",
        "Steps:\n",
        "1. Build user×movie and movie×user matrices, fill NaN with 0.\n",
        "2. Display a sample **user-user** and **item-item** similarity matrix (for demonstration).\n",
        "3. Convert the sparse matrix to a **CSR matrix** for efficiency.\n",
        "4. Use **KNN (NearestNeighbors)** with cosine metric to find 5 movies similar to a given movie."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "tmHUDcEPptzk"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from sklearn.metrics.pairwise import cosine_similarity\n",
        "\n",
        "# Fill NaN with 0 on the pivot table\n",
        "mat_filled = movie_matrix.fillna(0)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---- USER-USER similarity (demo on a small subset to keep it readable) ----\n",
        "user_sample = mat_filled.iloc[:5]          # first 5 users\n",
        "user_sim = cosine_similarity(user_sample)\n",
        "user_sim_df = pd.DataFrame(user_sim, index=user_sample.index, columns=user_sample.index)\n",
        "print(\"User-User Similarity Matrix (sample of 5 users):\")\n",
        "display(user_sim_df.round(3))\n",
        "\n",
        "# ---- ITEM-ITEM similarity (demo on a small subset) ----\n",
        "item_sample = mat_filled.iloc[:, :5]       # first 5 movies\n",
        "item_sim = cosine_similarity(item_sample.T)\n",
        "item_sim_df = pd.DataFrame(item_sim, index=item_sample.columns, columns=item_sample.columns)\n",
        "print(\"\\nItem-Item Similarity Matrix (sample of 5 movies):\")\n",
        "display(item_sim_df.round(3))"
      ],
