    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## Recommender System using Matrix Factorization (SVD)\n",
        "\n",
        "Matrix Factorization decomposes the large sparse user×item rating matrix into two smaller\n",
        "matrices of latent factors (embeddings) — one for users and one for items — of dimension `d`.\n",
        "Predicted rating = dot product of the user and item embedding vectors.\n",
        "\n",
        "We use the **Surprise** library's SVD with `n_factors = 4` (d = 4). We do a train-test split,\n",
        "train the model, and evaluate using **RMSE** and **MAPE**."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "RqH0FHe1qHr0"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "!pip install scikit-surprise -q"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "w8RjnZWnqI3W",
        "outputId": "4039b8f9-c94b-4b6c-98bd-bb7f893d10c2"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "\u001b[?25l   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m0.0/3.1 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m?\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m-:--:--\u001b[0m\r\u001b[2K   \u001b[91m━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[91m╸\u001b[0m\u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m0.3/3.1 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m9.0 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:01\u001b[0m\r\u001b[2K   \u001b[91m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m\u001b[90m╺\u001b[0m \u001b[32m3.0/3.1 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m42.9 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:01\u001b[0m\r\u001b[2K   \u001b[90m━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━\u001b[0m \u001b[32m3.1/3.1 MB\u001b[0m \u001b[31m29.4 MB/s\u001b[0m eta \u001b[36m0:00:00\u001b[0m\n",
            "\u001b[?25h"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "from surprise import Dataset, Reader, SVD\n",
        "from surprise.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
        "from surprise import accuracy\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "# Surprise expects: user, item, rating\n",
        "reader = Reader(rating_scale=(1, 5))\n",
        "data = Dataset.load_from_df(ratings[['UserID','MovieID','Rating']], reader)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Train-test split (Bonus question: yahi MF ka train-test split hai)\n",
        "trainset, testset = train_test_split(data, test_size=0.2, random_state=42)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Matrix Factorization with d = 4 latent factors\n",
        "svd = SVD(n_factors=4, random_state=42)\n",
        "svd.fit(trainset)\n",
        "predictions = svd.test(testset)\n",
        "print(\"Model trained. Number of test predictions:\", len(predictions))"
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "colab": {
          "base_uri": "https://localhost:8080/"
        },
        "id": "3oBT6nz8qQO9",
        "outputId": "f03c2107-ba63-4748-ed44-1b92d24edbbd"
      },
      "execution_count": null,
      "outputs": [
        {
          "output_type": "stream",
          "name": "stdout",
          "text": [
            "Model trained. Number of test predictions: 200042\n"
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "# RMSE\n",
        "rmse = accuracy.rmse(predictions, verbose=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# MAPE (manually compute)\n",
        "y_true = np.array([pred.r_ui for pred in predictions])\n",
        "y_pred = np.array([pred.est  for pred in predictions])\n",
        "mape = np.mean(np.abs((y_true - y_pred) / y_true)) * 100\n",
        "\n",
        "print(f\"\\nRMSE: {rmse:.4f}\")\n",
        "print(f\"MAPE: {mape:.2f}%\")\n",
        "print(\"\\nQ10 Answer — RMSE and MAPE above (note these values).\")"
      ],
