    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Analysis of d=2 Embeddings\n",
        "The 2D embedding plot maps each movie into a 2-dimensional latent space learned purely\n",
        "from rating patterns. Movies that are rated similarly by users appear close together,\n",
        "forming loose clusters, while dissimilar movies are pushed apart. This shows that matrix\n",
        "factorization captures hidden structure (e.g. genre/taste patterns) without ever being\n",
        "told the genres explicitly. Compared to raw cosine similarity on the full sparse matrix,\n",
        "these low-dimensional embeddings are far more compact and computationally efficient,\n",
        "though some fine-grained information is lost when compressing to just 2 dimensions."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "ihL_UH-sqx2R"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "## User-based Recommender using Pearson Correlation (Optional)\n",
        "\n",
        "Here a **new user** rates a few movies. We:\n",
        "1. Find old users who watched the same movies.\n",
        "2. Sort them by number of movies in common, take the top 100.\n",
        "3. Compute a Pearson similarity score between the new user and each.\n",
        "4. Take the top 10 most similar users.\n",
        "5. Weight their movie ratings by similarity and recommend the highest-scoring movies."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "BSt-YY3pq4U2"
      }
    },
